               <sense xml:lang="la" source="#dillmann" xml:id="Dmain"> et <foreign xml:lang="gez">ደርከኖ፡</foreign> <gramGrp> <pos expand="Substantivum">subst.</pos> </gramGrp> [a radice <foreign xml:lang="gez">ረከነ፡</foreign> i.e. <foreign xml:lang="he">רגם רקם</foreign> <foreign xml:lang="ar">رقن</foreign> ductum et cum <foreign xml:lang="he">אַרְגָּמָן</foreign> <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܐܪܰܓܘܳܢܳܐ</foreign> cognatum (de <foreign xml:lang="gez">ደ</foreign> vid. <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:Dillmann1857Gramm"/>gramm.</bibl> § 73) videtur, et mihi quidem hoc etymon probabilius est quam si quis vocabulum a <foreign xml:lang="ar">زرق</foreign> duxerit] <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la">
